 form of <b>Mag Mhuirneacháin</b> ‘son of <i>Muirneachán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>muirneach</i> ‘lovable’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Thomas De Gordon was born in 1185, in Gordon, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Sir Thomas de Gordon, Knight, 3rd Laird of Gordon. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1185–":"1185–Surnud","1183–1260":"1183–1260","1214–1259":"1214–1259","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1259":"1259","1214":"1214","1185":"1185","1260":"1260","1183":"1183","Gordon Berwickshire, Scotland":"Gordon, Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kelso, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Kelso, Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1185–":"1185–Kuollut","1183–1260":"1183–1260","1214–1259":"1214–1259","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1214":"1214","1185":"1185","1260":"1260","1183":"1183","Gordon Berwickshire, Scotland":"Gordon, Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kelso, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Kelso, Roxburghshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1185–":"1185–Décédée","1183–1260":"1183–1260","1214–1259":"1214–1259","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","1259":"1259","1214":"1214","1185":"1185","1260":"1260","1183":"1183","Gordon Berwickshire, Scotland":"Gordon, Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Kelso, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Kelso, Roxburghshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs Thomas De Gordon est née en 1185, à Gordon, Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Sir Thomas de Gordon, Knight, 3rd Lair